HARVEY.name: Harvey AI
HARVEY.tagline: Domain-specific AI platform transforming legal and professional services with frontier AI
HARVEY.overview: Harvey AI is a pioneering legal technology company founded in 2022 by Winston Weinberg and Gabriel Pereyra. The company specializes in domain-specific artificial intelligence for legal and professional services sectors. Harvey provides AI-powered solutions for tasks such as contract analysis, due diligence, legal research, compliance, and litigation support. Its platform is used by global law firms and Fortune 500 enterprises. As of June 2025, Harvey achieved a $5 billion valuation following a $300 million Series E funding round. The company reached $100 million in annual recurring revenue in August 2025, serving over 500 customers across 54 countries, including 42% of AmLaw 100 firms.

HIPPOCRATIC-AI.name: Hippocratic AI
HIPPOCRATIC-AI.tagline: Building the safest generative AI healthcare agents to bring clinical abundance and close the global healthcare worker shortage
HIPPOCRATIC-AI.overview: Hippocratic AI is the global leader in safety-focused generative AI healthcare agents, founded in 2023 by CEO Munjal Shah alongside physicians, hospital administrators, healthcare professionals, and AI researchers from leading institutions including El Camino Health, Johns Hopkins, Washington University in St. Louis, Stanford, Google, and NVIDIA. The company's mission is to develop the safest Large Language Model for healthcare, bringing clinical abundance to address the growing shortage of 15 million healthcare workers worldwide. Named after the Hippocratic Oath, the company prioritizes "Do No Harm" above all else, focusing exclusively on non-diagnostic, patient-facing clinical tasks. As of November 2025, Hippocratic AI has achieved a $3.5 billion valuation following its Series C round, establishing partnerships with over 50 large health systems, payors, and pharma clients across 6 countries, completing over 115 million patient interactions with zero safety issues.

highlights.text: Hippocratic AI continues to grow and expand

HUGGING-FACE.name: Hugging Face
HUGGING-FACE.tagline: The AI community building the future with open-source models, datasets, and collaborative spaces
HUGGING-FACE.overview: Hugging Face is the leading open-source AI platform founded in 2016, providing a hub for machine learning models, datasets, and collaborative applications. Originally a chatbot startup, the company pivoted to become the 'GitHub of AI,' hosting over 800,000 models and 200,000 datasets. Hugging Face's Transformers library is the most popular ML library on GitHub. With a $4.5 billion valuation after raising $235M in Series D funding led by Salesforce, Google, and NVIDIA, the company serves major enterprises including Apple, Google, Meta, and Microsoft. The platform enables developers to discover, share, and deploy AI models for free.
